 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Critical Buckling Examples With Varying Boundary Conditions\n",
    "\n",
    "Thanks the Bardell equations implamentation, composipy is capable of simulating different boundary conditions and different combinations of load cases.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Importing composipy objects and creating properties"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from composipy import OrthotropicMaterial, LaminateProperty\n",
    "from composipy import PlateStructure\n",
    "import matplotlib"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Ply Material Properties (MPa and mm)\n",
    "E1 = 60800\n",
    "E2 = 58250\n",
    "v12 = 0.07\n",
    "G12 = 4550\n",
    "t = 0.21\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plate Parameters (mm)\n",
    "a = 360.\n",
    "b = 360.\n",
    "m = 10 # discretization in x direction\n",
    "n = 10 # discretization in y direction\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Stacking sequence\n",
    "stacking = [45,-45,0,90,45,-45,0,90,45,-45]\n",
    "stacking += stacking[::-1] # symmetry"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Ply material and laminate property objects\n",
    "\n",
    "ply_1 = OrthotropicMaterial(E1, E2, v12, G12, t)\n",
    "l1 = LaminateProperty(stacking, ply_1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Pinned Nxx"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "panel_SSSS = PlateStructure(l1, a, b, m=m, n=n, Nxx=-1,constraints='PINNED')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "eigvals, eigvecs = panel_SSSS.buckling_analysis()"
   ]
  },
  {
